items.title: Medtronic explores options to optimize manufacturing operations amid Trump's tariff threats
items.description: The company, whose products range from insulin pumps to surgical robots, has been closely monitoring Trump’s tariff plans due to its presence in Mexico.

items.title: India mulls $1 billion subsidy plan to boost solar manufacturing
items.description: The proposal is being made by the Ministry of New and Renewable Energy and will target domestic makers of wafers and ingots, one of the weakest segments of the country’s solar industry, according to the people, who asked not to be identified as the discussions are private.

items.title: Maruti Suzuki commissions first phase of added capacity at Haryana's Kharkhoda plant
items.description: The car maker has said in the past that it is preparing for an increased competitive intensity in India's automotive space, which will improve the manufacturing standard as well as expand the market.

items.title: Repco Home Finance: Focused on affordable housing loans, undervalued
items.description: Core portfolio growth, geographical diversification will drive scale

items.title: Will Trump’s tariffs assail Indian pharma, or can it sail through?
items.description: In 2024, India exported drugs worth around $8.73 billion to the US —  about 31 percent of its total pharma exports, while the US exported $635.37 million worth of pharmaceuticals to India.

items.title: Akzo Nobel India accepts binding offer from promoter firm for powder coating & r&d biz
items.description: The execution of these transactions remains subject to the approval of the shareholders of Akzo Nobel India Limited and approval of the Supervisory Board of Akzo Nobel N.V.
